The evidence with the title 'Arms Trade Treaty - Wikipedia ' says The Arms Trade Treaty (ATT) is a multilateral treaty that regulates the international trade in conventional weapons . It entered into force on 24 december 2014 . Ninety-two states have ratified the treaty, and a further 41 states have signed but not ratified it . The ATT is an attempt to regulate the international trade of conventional  ... International weapons commerce has been estimated to reach US$ 70 billion  ... 
